  "text": "When observations are not regular, the AVAR is equal to 2T T Our aim is to allow for parametric noise in this endogenous setting, while also including jumps in the price process. As far as the authors know, no general theory 6 includes general endogeneity and jumps, even when observations are not noisy. Accordingly, we first extend the results of [CITATION_1] when adding jumps. Then, we show that the technology of this paper applies in such a general setting.",
